ðŸ§© What is a Divider in Jetpack Compose:-
* A Divider is a lightweight horizontal (or vertical) line used to separate content visually in a layout. It is similar to <hr> in HTML.
* Dividers are thin lines that separate items in lists or other containers. 
* You can implement dividers in your app using the HorizontalDivider and VerticalDivider composables.
    1. HorizontalDivider: Separate items in a column.
    2. VerticalDivider: Separate items in a row.


âœ… Why Use a Divider:--
* Improves visual hierarchy.
* Groups or separates sections or components.
* Helps enhance UI readability.


API surface:---
* Both components provide parameters for modifying their appearance:
    1. thickness: Use this parameter to specify the thickness of the divider line.
    2. color: Use this parameter to specify the color of the divider line.    


ðŸ§¾ Best Practices:-
* Keep the divider subtle to avoid clutter.
* Use paddings for proper spacing.
* Prefer using divider with lists or complex UIs where visual separation is needed.    


